  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Lodestar should disconnect on hello:\n1. If `fork_version` doesn’t match the local fork version, since the client’s chain is on another fork. `fork_version` can also be used to segregate testnets.\n2. If the (`finalized_root`, `finalized_epoch`) shared by the peer is not in the client's chain at the expected epoch. For example, if Peer 1 sends (root, epoch) of (A, 5) and Peer 2 sends (B, 3) but Peer 1 has root C at epoch 3, then Peer 1 would disconnect because it knows that their chains are irreparably disjoint.",
